        textEn: 'Dogme 95 was a manifesto written by directors Lars von Trier (born 1956) and Thomas Vinterberg (born 1969). They committed themselves to making simple films with a focus on good storytelling. Lars von Trier won the Palme d\'Or for Dancer in the Dark (2000).',
        vocabRefs: ['Dogme 95', 'Lars von Trier', 'Thomas Vinterberg']
